5:
Hah-hah!
As they say, "A true knight never fails
to find his catch!"
9:
You're just making those up at this
point! And I thought we said NO
MORE MONSTERS? Don't knock 'em
into the main pile!
20:
Hah-hah-hah!
Why do you struggle so, little fish? It
is no use!
24:
See how my trident pierces the
water effortlessly! With it—and my
precious flotation device—I am
UNSTOPPABLE!
26:
Yes, in a past life, I was no doubt an
artisan fisherman! Such is my
preternatural skill!
32:
Everyone! Look at this MASSIVE one I
just fished up—
37:
Welcome back, Gerard! You've got
more fish for us, huh?
43:
Holy—that thing is huge! I can't wait
to get that on the grill! In small
pieces, of course.
50:
You... were fighting monsters? By
yourselves?
53:
Huh? I mean, yeah, but they were
just small fry! No big deal, really. You
were so into fishing, we didn't want
to interrupt you.
59:
"A true knight always comes to the
aid of those in need."
And yet... I... failed to.
68:
What the? Er... Should we go after
him?
72:
Nah. I have a feeling he'll be right
back.
76: Let this mark the END of my vacation!
83:
I have seen the error of my ways!
Never again shall I display such
cowardice! This I swear here, to you
all!
86:
My first duty shall be a patrol of the
vicinity—rest at ease, I will ensure
that your vacation is a safe one!
99:
What can you do...
That armor doesn't look comfortable
in this weather though. Think he'll be
okay?
103:
He really takes his duty seriously...
Perhaps it's best to leave him be
until he's satisfied.
111: Yes, we are forever grateful to you!
114:
Hah-hah! 'Twas really nothing!
But young lass, I must caution
you—be careful to never again stray
far from your lady mother!
119:
Well, the people sure seem to like
him. He's doing good work.
... Even though we're supposed to be
on vacation.
122:
Like Light said, just leave him alone.
Let the guy do what he wants.
127:
I think it'd be more interesting if we
stuck with him for a bit longer, don't
you?
138:
Hah! Excellent! I... helped out so
many people today...
Oh dear, I feel... dizzy...
142:
Gerard! Are you okay—
OUCH! Your armor is boiling hot!
146:
Them's the breaks... Let's find him
some shade.
155: Nice to see you've come to.
159:
Your armor seems to have cooled
off. You should be fine now.
162:
I see... I must have collapsed due to
the heat. I'm sorry for causing you so
much trouble...
166:
Don't worry about it. First things first,
you should really consider taking off
that armor!
170:
B-but... This is the formal garb of a
proper knight! I can't...
176:
Oh for cryin' out loud... Take it off!
You're gonna boil alive in there!
181:
With an outfit like this, I can no
longer call myself a knight...
184:
I don't see a problem—we're on
vacation after all! You don't need to
be a knight all the time.
189:
But... If my friends were to be
exposed to danger, all while I was
out making merry... That would be a
disgrace to my station as a knight!
193:
Where does it say that knights aren't
allowed to "make merry"?
201:
Knights need rest too, Gerard! I know
I've definitely seen knights in
Palpebra on their days off!
203:
We're on vacation! Why not take a
short break from being a knight?
207:
A... vacation... But... For me, being a
knight is not merely a profession. It
is more... a way of life! How can I
stop being who—
212:
All right, I've had enough of all this
knight talk.
Alk, I'm borrowing him for a while,
okay?
216:
B-borrowing? Where are you taking
me?!
219:
Relax, it's nowhere bad. Just a place
where you can loosen up, mellow
out, you know.
224:
Wait a moment! I know what lies in
this direction! Why would you be
taking me THERE?!
227:
Heh, so you know what's over here?
That means... you did some
research beforehand! Busted.
235:
Th-that is emphatically wrong! I
merely, uh... read that such a place
exists... in a guidebook, yes!
238:
Heh. Let's go check it out for
ourselves, just to make sure it's
there. "A true knight's gotta know
when to party hard," as they say.
241:
They don't say that!
...Do they? I've never heard that one!
244:
Oh yeah, they definitely do. All the
big city knights say that.
248:
Now you're just confusing the poor
guy.
